'''Yuzusame Shrine''' (ゆずさめじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Tsuruoka|Q734416|WD=Q734416|1=Tsuruoka}}, {{ill|lt=Yamagata Prefecture|Q125863|WD=Q125863|1=Yamagata Prefecture}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
*Center seat: {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Mizokuihime-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}} (みぞくいひめのみこと)
*Left seat: {{ill|Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|lt=Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|WD=Q276944|1=Ōkuninushi}}
*Right seat: {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Sukunahikona-no-Mikoto|1=Sukunabikona|WD=Q3275687}}

=== Overview ===
It is said to have been founded in {{ill|lt=Hakuchi|Q540118|WD=Q540118|1=Hakuchi (era)}} 1 ({{ill|lt=650|Q30179|WD=Q30179|1=650}}). It was formerly called Kannon-dō, Yukura Gongen, Ryūzō Gongen, and from old times has been revered by local residents as the shrine protecting {{ill|lt=Yutagawa Onsen|Q11563759|WD=Q11563759|1=Yutagawa Onsen}}. Its former rank under the {{ill|lt=modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|WD=Q712534|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}} was gōsha (ranked in {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 9 / {{ill|lt=1876|Q7766|WD=Q7766|1=1876}}), and it is also a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} recorded in the ''{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}'', making it a shrine of long-standing tradition. The current main sanctuary was expanded in Meiji 15 ({{ill|lt=1882|Q7812|WD=Q7812|1=1882}}) by master shrine carpenter Takahashi Kanekichi.

In late April 2002 (Heisei 14), location filming for the movie ''{{ill|lt=The Twilight Samurai#Film|Q94033|WD=Q94033|lt=The Twilight Samurai|1=The Twilight Samurai}}'' was carried out at this shrine<ref>[https://www.yamagata-np.jp/feature/fujisawa_sekai/kj_2017040600239.php 藤沢周平没後20年、生誕90年] Yamagata Shimbun (April 6, 2017)</ref>. An information board on the approach records details of the filming at that time.

<gallery>
Tsuruoka city Yuzusamejinja stone steps approach.jpg|Stone steps of Yuzusame Shrine
</gallery>

=== Access ===
*From {{ill|lt=Tsuruoka Station|Q7850300|WD=Q7850300|1=Tsuruoka Station}} on the {{ill|lt=Uetsu Main Line|Q1056211|WD=Q1056211|1=Uetsu Main Line}} of {{ill|lt=JR East|Q499071|WD=Q499071|lt=JR|1=East Japan Railway Company}}, about 20 minutes by bus operated by {{ill|lt=Shonai Kōtsū|Q11485800|WD=Q11485800|1=Shonai Kotsu}}
